public class ReusableEqualityHelper
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.util.EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper

An class to be used or extended by clients to compare EObjects that can be used for multiple comparisons in order to avoid comparing the same object trees twice. The implementation is based on EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper.

equals

public boolean equals(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject eObject1,
                      org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject eObject2)
A re-implementation of EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper.equals(EObject, EObject)that makes instances ready for reuse for multiple comparisons.

As EqualityHelper only uses methods from the inherited HashMap in the method equals(EObject, EObject) it is sufficient to override this method to make EqualityHelper helper reusable for multiple comparisons.

The developers of EcoreUtil.EqualityHelper assumed (as stated in the JavaDoc) that an EObject is equal to at most one EObject because they assumed that for each new comparison a new Helper will be used. The corresponding discussion can be found at bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=369653.

The bug that an entry is never removed in cases where this method returns false was fixed in a new release: bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=369651.
